Modified Browne Data - Motivation for Modifications

Florian Stijven

2023-08-23

In this document, we justify the choices to add additional effects of covariates on the outcomes in the original Browne data. We only consider CESD at 6 months as outcome. These additional effects are artificially added to illustrate some ideas that cannot be illustrated with the original data because these (interaction) effects are not present there. We consider three artificial data sets.

  1. We add a treatment-interaction effect for past major depressive disorder (MDD) (past_MDD) and baseline CESD (cesd) for their effect on CESD at 6 months (cesd2). So, these two baseline covariates are artificially turned into treatment effect modifiers.
  2. In addition to the changes in the first point, we add a quadratic effect for the main effect of age. So, the outcome regression model that we have used before will be misspecified.
  3. In addition to the changes in the first point, we add a three-way interaction for treatment-past MDD-age. The outcome regression model does not include three-way interactions and will thus again be missspecified. In addition, this three-way interaction is not captured by the class of linear treatment regimes that we are considering.

We first give some results and plots for the original data where we do an available case analysis to deal with the missing data. This provides a reference to compare the updated data sets with. The goal is to change the original data in such a way that the modified data are still plausible.

1 Original data

2 Update 1

The first update involves the introduction of additional treatment effect heterogeneity. The modification of the outcome variable is as follows, \[\tilde{\texttt{cesd2}} = \texttt{cesd2} - (0.30 \cdot (\texttt{cesd} - 40) - 6 \cdot \texttt{past_MDD}) \cdot I(\texttt{group} = 1) + 0.20 \cdot (\texttt{cesd} - 40) + 4 \cdot \texttt{past_MDD}\] where a tilde indicates the updated value and group \(1\) corresponds to Sertraline and IPT. Patients will thus benefit more Sertraline and IPT (as compared to Sertraline alone) if they have a more severe depression at baseline (larger CESD and past MDD).

We next repeat the same regression models and plots as before. There now is a signficant interaction effect for past MDD and baseline CESD. Note also that there is a slight change in R-squared.

3 Update 2

The second update involves the introduction of a quadratic main effect of age that leads to our outcome model being misspecified. The modification of the outcome variable is as follows, \[\tilde{\texttt{cesd2}} = \texttt{cesd2} + 0.01 \cdot (\texttt{age} - 25)^2. \] where a tilde indicates the updated value and \(\texttt{cesd2}\) is the value from the first update.

This is a quadratic main effect of age. Patients will thus do worse on average if they are further away from 25 years old. Since most patients are older than 25, this basically means that younger patients will do better.

We next repeat the same regression models and plots as before. Beside treatment effect heterogeneity, there is now evidence for a quadratic main effect of age (as shown in the last plot).

4 Update 3

The third update involves the introduction of additional treatment effect heterogeneity that leads the our outcome regression model being misspecified. The modification of the outcome variable is as follows, \[\tilde{\texttt{cesd2}} = \texttt{cesd2} - 0.2 \cdot (\texttt{age} - 50) \cdot \texttt{past_MDD} \cdot I(\texttt{group} = 1) \] where a tilde indicates the updated value and \(\texttt{cesd2}\) is the value from the first update. This corresponds to a three-way interaction. Because of this, the outcome regression model will be misspecified. In contrast to update 2, the misspecification is now in the interaction terms instead of the main effects (as was the case for update 2). This also means that the class of linear regimes that we are considering does not contain the optimal regime.

We next repeat the same regression models and plots as before. The other plots ar similar to those from update 1, although there now is an additional three-way interaction.
